HEADWORD: Spalpeen
<hw>Spal"peen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ir.
<ets>spailpin</ets>, fr. <ets>spailp</ets> a beau, pride,
self-conceit.]</ety> <def>A scamp; an Irish term for a good-for-nothing
fellow; -- often used in good-humored contempt or ridicule.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

